01:19.580 --> 01:20.912
Help!

01:22.124 --> 01:23.911
Someone help!

01:25.085 --> 01:26.075
Help!

02:48.960 --> 02:50.997
<i>Paging Dr Jones.</i>

02:51.046 --> 02:53.413
<i>- Paging Dr Jones.</i>
- Lee.

02:53.465 --> 02:55.707
Lee, you know I can only help you

02:55.759 --> 02:58.092
if you're willing to take a step
towards me, Lee.

02:59.179 --> 03:02.297
I thought that we had an understanding.

03:02.349 --> 03:04.215
Was I wrong?

03:05.435 --> 03:09.179
People need my help for
all sorts of reasons.

03:09.231 --> 03:11.393
Some have broken hearts...

03:12.567 --> 03:14.854
...others have broken heads.

03:14.903 --> 03:17.771
Then there's those too young
to know better...

03:19.866 --> 03:22.779
...those running away from their past...

03:23.954 --> 03:26.446
...and those who are just lost.

03:26.498 --> 03:30.208
Until you can tell me which one you are,
we're done.

03:31.336 --> 03:34.044
We'll review things again
in six months' time.

03:34.089 --> 03:36.627
Craig, if you could please
take Lee to the ward.

03:36.675 --> 03:37.836
Certainly, Dr Jones.

03:39.553 --> 03:41.044
Morning, Fred.

03:41.096 --> 03:42.712
Be back with you in a minute.

03:42.764 --> 03:45.757
You can put some clothes back on, Rosie.

03:45.809 --> 03:47.095
Morning, Lee.

04:07.539 --> 04:10.031
Er... This is a crime scene.

04:11.334 --> 04:12.791
I live right there.

05:07.933 --> 05:09.549
Oi, where you heading?

05:12.062 --> 05:13.223
That way.

05:14.397 --> 05:15.558
Where you goin'?

05:17.609 --> 05:18.895
Don't know.

05:21.363 --> 05:22.979
Need a ride?

05:24.866 --> 05:26.152
No thanks.

05:26.201 --> 05:28.033
It's gonna rain.

05:30.038 --> 05:32.621
There's a lotta weird people around here,
ya know?

05:32.666 --> 05:34.498
Yeah, I bet.

05:34.543 --> 05:37.661
This is a lonely road.
You'll wait ages for another lift.

05:48.932 --> 05:53.267
Excuse me, how much longer will this take?
I... I have other patients to attend to.

05:53.311 --> 05:55.303
It takes as long as it takes, Dr Jones.

05:55.355 --> 05:59.474
Bearing in mind that you run one of
the most secure facilities in the country,

05:59.526 --> 06:01.813
how could one of your most
dangerous inmates escape?

06:01.862 --> 06:04.775
They're not inmates, they're...
they're, they're patients.

06:04.823 --> 06:06.860
They need treatment, they're ill.

06:06.908 --> 06:09.525
Lee Hunting, born October 31st 1985.

06:09.578 --> 06:12.116
Quiet child, never really bonded with
other children.

06:12.163 --> 06:13.495
While a teenager... Excuse me!

06:13.540 --> 06:16.123
Quiet child, never really bonded
with other children,

06:16.167 --> 06:19.501
something about throwing darts
at their backs in the playground.

06:19.546 --> 06:22.710
While a teenager, developed
a bit of a thing for knives,

06:22.757 --> 06:24.248
self-harming for practice

06:24.301 --> 06:28.341
before turning the blades on four family
members on Christmas Day 2002.

06:28.388 --> 06:31.847
I guess the Queen's speech brings out
the worst in all of us, ma'am.

06:33.935 --> 06:37.804
Just shy of the 18th birthday,
treated as a minor,

06:37.856 --> 06:40.473
and kept in the cushy confines
of an establishment such as yours.

06:40.525 --> 06:42.983
- All right, that's enough.
- Instead of rotting in a class A prison

06:43.028 --> 06:45.065
- along with all other murderous nutters.
- Excuse me,

06:45.113 --> 06:48.356
but we try to help our patients live out
normal lives as much as they can.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.195
We try not to dwell too much on the past,

06:50.243 --> 06:54.078
and we certainly don't like to call
our patients murderous nutters.

06:54.122 --> 06:56.159
Call them what you wish, Dr Jones.

06:56.207 --> 06:59.541
This dangerous individual is now free on
my patch because of you,

06:59.586 --> 07:02.624
so excuse me if I'm being a little
curt with you today,

07:02.672 --> 07:06.461
but I've got nutters to catch,
people to protect,

07:06.509 --> 07:10.093
and in my experience, time is everything,
so stop cocking me around

07:10.138 --> 07:12.050
- and let me do my fucking job.
- You have no idea...

07:12.098 --> 07:14.806
what you're getting yourself into.

07:20.440 --> 07:23.103
Henry, you can give us
another chance, right?

07:23.151 --> 07:26.770
I will promise you that the company
will make it worth your while.

07:26.821 --> 07:30.861
Look, Tim, you're a nice guy, mate,
but I've had enough.

07:30.909 --> 07:33.026
You and me, we do a deal on prices,

07:33.078 --> 07:36.116
but then that cock boss of yours, Derrick,
moves the goalpost

07:36.164 --> 07:37.826
every time an invoice shows up.

07:37.874 --> 07:42.164
When I complain, he either sends me
an unsigned cheque

07:42.212 --> 07:45.205
or one with the wrong fucking year on it,
so I can't even cash it.

07:47.008 --> 07:51.548
Right, okay, well look, Henry,
I am very sorry about that.

07:51.596 --> 07:53.132
It's not your fault, Tim.

07:53.181 --> 07:56.140
To be honest, we all feel a bit sorry
for you around here.

07:56.184 --> 07:59.803
Workin' for an arsehole like that
can't be easy, but...

08:00.897 --> 08:02.809
...I've gotta protect my business.

08:02.857 --> 08:05.315
Quite right, Henry, quite right.

08:06.444 --> 08:08.606
Okay, but listen, what if I...?

08:08.655 --> 08:12.569
Your delivery guys only deliver
in this area on a Wednesday.

08:13.827 --> 08:15.568
I play golf on a Wednesday.

08:16.663 --> 08:19.246
- Could someone else not be here to...?
- No.

08:20.583 --> 08:21.573
Toddle off.

08:47.986 --> 08:49.318
Why have we stopped?

08:49.362 --> 08:53.732
Regulations. Can only drive for so long
without takin' a break, it's the law.

08:56.745 --> 08:58.452
Thanks for the ride.

08:58.496 --> 09:00.158
You got a name?

09:02.042 --> 09:03.408
Zoe.

09:05.211 --> 09:06.543
Pretty.

09:09.049 --> 09:10.711
I should really get going.

09:10.759 --> 09:12.216
What's the rush?

09:13.344 --> 09:14.460
- No!
- Oh yeah.

09:14.512 --> 09:15.878
No, stop!

09:15.930 --> 09:17.717
Stop!

09:17.766 --> 09:19.098
Help!

09:52.383 --> 09:54.045
Hello, Dexter.

09:58.640 --> 10:01.474
I was surprised you wanted to see me, Max.

10:02.894 --> 10:05.102
Of course I wanted to see ya.

10:05.146 --> 10:08.765
I just always assumed that you probably
blamed me for what happened with Molly.

10:10.527 --> 10:12.268
You know, there's...

10:13.696 --> 10:16.029
There's not a day goes by
when I don't think about Molly.

10:18.284 --> 10:20.947
She was my daughter.

10:20.995 --> 10:23.408
My only daughter.

10:24.874 --> 10:27.708
You were like a son.

10:27.752 --> 10:31.211
Losin' her like that was, no...

10:31.256 --> 10:32.246
tears me apart.

10:33.299 --> 10:35.382
Me too.

10:35.426 --> 10:37.463
But you have to move on, don't you?

10:37.512 --> 10:39.674
That's the way she woulda wanted.

10:41.474 --> 10:44.217
One million pounds.

10:44.269 --> 10:45.680
What?

10:45.728 --> 10:50.644
In two days' time, a jeep will be passing
through here on its way to the airport.

10:50.692 --> 10:54.185
Onboard is six million pounds.

10:54.237 --> 10:58.322
Our European cousins, they're movin'
some assets offshore.

10:58.366 --> 11:00.403
At least that's what they think.

11:00.451 --> 11:02.613
I want you to steal it.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.321
How'd you even know about it?

11:05.373 --> 11:08.241
And our money ain't
what it used to be, Dex,

11:08.293 --> 11:12.253
but you can still do a lot
with a million pounds.

11:14.299 --> 11:17.542
You can move away from
all these bad memories.

11:17.594 --> 11:20.678
Go somewhere warm, buy yourself a bar,

11:20.722 --> 11:23.089
spend the rest of your days
drinkin' the profits.

11:24.184 --> 11:26.096
You just got to do one last job.

11:27.645 --> 11:28.726
Who gets the rest?

11:28.771 --> 11:30.262
Me.

11:30.315 --> 11:32.898
Oh, and the tip, of course.

11:34.777 --> 11:36.018
My own crew?

11:39.824 --> 11:42.441
You can take Al and that lunatic Topic.

11:43.494 --> 11:45.531
The other side want two
of their people on.

11:46.706 --> 11:48.038
Just in case, ya know?

11:48.082 --> 11:49.914
Guys I've never worked with?

11:52.962 --> 11:54.624
Not exactly.

12:13.691 --> 12:15.774
How'd it go with, er...?

12:15.818 --> 12:17.104
- Probation?
- Mm.

12:18.196 --> 12:20.779
Twenty minutes of playbook
before cuttin' me a benefits slip,

12:20.823 --> 12:23.691
tellin' me to keep out of trouble
and away from bad influences.

12:23.743 --> 12:25.860
You come to the wrong place then, mate.

12:28.289 --> 12:29.905
Oh, Jesus Christ!

12:29.958 --> 12:31.574
Not quite.

12:38.341 --> 12:39.673
Dex.

12:50.144 --> 12:54.229
So... how was Her Majesty's pleasure?

12:54.274 --> 12:56.061
Was she as good for you as she was for me?

12:59.070 --> 13:00.732
You remember Al.

13:00.780 --> 13:02.442
Hm...

13:02.490 --> 13:04.903
Done some time with you, no?

13:06.244 --> 13:09.783
Gotta say, Max really knows
how to pick the best of the bunch.

13:12.041 --> 13:15.159
So, Dex, you up to this, yeah?

13:15.211 --> 13:17.669
Hey, we'll get the job done.

13:18.798 --> 13:19.914
Who are you?

13:19.966 --> 13:22.049
- This is, er...
- Duffy.

13:22.093 --> 13:23.300
Duffy.

13:23.344 --> 13:25.677
Where's Topic, Duffy?

13:25.722 --> 13:27.304
He's in the car.

13:27.348 --> 13:30.011
Don't worry about nuttin',
finish up your drink.

13:32.312 --> 13:34.599
They say if you're gonna drink
with the devil,

13:34.647 --> 13:37.105
sup from a very short spoon.

13:38.735 --> 13:41.352
I'm done. Let's get on with it.

13:43.990 --> 13:46.323
It's long spoon. Let's go.

14:01.341 --> 14:04.925
Oh, dear God, okay, well let's just go
through this again then one more time.

14:04.969 --> 14:07.427
Oh, how many fuckin' times?

14:07.472 --> 14:10.340
As many times as it takes, Topic.
I don't like to take chances.

14:10.391 --> 14:12.849
It's like the education rooms
in the clink.

14:12.894 --> 14:15.102
Some know-it-all givin' it all that.

14:16.397 --> 14:17.558
Fuck's sake!

14:17.607 --> 14:18.688
Do you wanna go back?

14:18.733 --> 14:20.770
I hear you're missed in the showers.

14:20.818 --> 14:21.808
I don't.

14:22.904 --> 14:25.863
So we just keep goin' through this
until we get it right, yeah?

14:25.907 --> 14:26.943
I'm just sayin'...

14:26.991 --> 14:29.950
We've been through it
a million times already.

14:29.994 --> 14:31.735
We know what we have to do, yeah?

14:31.788 --> 14:34.826
Really? All right. What's that?

14:39.629 --> 14:42.167
Look, why don't we just
keep this simple?

14:42.215 --> 14:45.333
The security van with the money
approaches from the southeast.

14:45.385 --> 14:51.052
While you, Dexter, you run interference,
and Al here pretends he's directing Topic.

14:51.099 --> 14:54.683
Then, you knock out the driver and
his mate,

14:54.727 --> 14:57.344
while I make sure he doesn't think about
reversin' out of there.

14:57.397 --> 15:00.515
Boys give up the keys, eat the dirt.

15:00.566 --> 15:03.775
We lift the coins, get the fuck out,

15:03.820 --> 15:07.985
come back here, divvy it up, and split.

15:08.032 --> 15:09.864
Always about the money, eh?

15:10.952 --> 15:13.160
You make it sound so simple, Fordy.

15:13.204 --> 15:15.742
It is so simple, Dex.

15:15.790 --> 15:19.830
Not unless you're feelin' a bit rusty.
Wanna call Max, find someone else?

15:21.003 --> 15:25.964
Otherwise, you do your job, we do ours.

15:35.435 --> 15:36.846
24 hours.

15:37.937 --> 15:40.520
Okay, that's enough, people.

15:40.565 --> 15:43.228
Mouths shut and ears open.

15:44.318 --> 15:46.275
We are 18 hours in.

15:47.321 --> 15:49.984
And so far, we have no sightings,
no leads,

15:50.032 --> 15:54.948
and the time is rapidly approaching
before something fucking big happens.

15:54.996 --> 16:00.367
Let me remind you that Lee Hunting
is a cold, callous, pathological killer.

16:00.418 --> 16:03.331
Forget what the white-coat do-gooders say.

16:03.379 --> 16:08.044
We're dealing with a homicidal psychopath
who kills without remorse or reason.

16:08.092 --> 16:12.553
Any form of sexual contact has
historically triggered a violent response.

16:12.597 --> 16:15.635
After what some thought had become
a deep and friendly relationship,

16:15.683 --> 16:19.142
one inmate got a little fresh with Lee
and got their throat cut.

16:19.187 --> 16:23.056
We have a long list of assaulted
prison guards, police officers,

16:23.107 --> 16:26.771
and it's only a matter of time
before Hunting kills.

16:27.862 --> 16:30.946
I know you're tired, people,
but caffeine up.

16:32.074 --> 16:35.363
Nobody is going home till we find
the trail of breadcrumbs.

16:42.543 --> 16:44.330
- What a bitch!
- Telling me!

18:02.039 --> 18:04.201
I can't believe it.

18:04.250 --> 18:07.038
I saw Mrs Jenner in here only yesterday.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.998
Her cleaning lady found her.

18:09.046 --> 18:10.753
She's very upset.

18:10.798 --> 18:13.882
I'm not surprised.
I know it's worrying, but what can we do?

18:13.926 --> 18:15.963
Well, what are the police gonna do
about it?

18:16.012 --> 18:17.924
I'm sure the police are doing
all they can.

18:17.972 --> 18:20.464
But this is the third one in a month.

18:20.516 --> 18:23.634
It's all right for you,
but I live on my own.

18:23.686 --> 18:25.393
We have our very own serial killer.

18:25.438 --> 18:27.395
Now, we don't know that.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.932
They found the woman
tied up and mutilated.

18:29.984 --> 18:32.567
Doesn't sound like the <i>Kama Sutra</i>
goin' wrong to me.

18:32.612 --> 18:33.728
Nor me.

18:35.656 --> 18:37.192
Who said she was mutilated?

18:37.241 --> 18:40.234
Her cleaner did.
She said there was blood everywhere.

18:41.621 --> 18:43.203
It must be an outsider.

18:44.290 --> 18:45.326
What must?

18:45.374 --> 18:46.785
The killer must be.

18:46.834 --> 18:47.870
Why?

18:47.918 --> 18:50.831
Because we all know each other
around here.

18:50.880 --> 18:52.667
It has to be someone new.

18:56.010 --> 18:59.299
Elliott, I've told you before

18:59.347 --> 19:02.215
not to throw the papers onto
the driveway or gardens.

19:02.266 --> 19:04.474
This isn't some American suburb.

19:04.518 --> 19:07.511
Take them up to the front door and
post them through the letterbox

19:07.563 --> 19:09.429
or find another job.

19:19.784 --> 19:21.650
- Nigel.
- Yes.

19:23.120 --> 19:24.986
Wonder if you can help me.

19:36.801 --> 19:39.794
Yeah, yes, I'm on my way there now.
Yeah.

19:39.845 --> 19:42.258
But, Derrick, sorry, um,
what's the guy's name again?

19:42.306 --> 19:45.674
Don't fuck this up, Tim, all right?
We need this contract.

19:45.726 --> 19:49.219
No contract, you don't get paid, ever,
comprende?

19:49.271 --> 19:51.638
Comprende, comprende,
I will not fuck up.

19:51.691 --> 19:53.432
I promise, Derrick, I swear for...

19:53.484 --> 19:55.646
<i>Derrick?</i>

19:55.695 --> 19:57.027
Derrick?

19:58.114 --> 20:00.857
Oh, Suse, how about a nosh-off
before lunch, hm?

20:02.201 --> 20:03.942
Fuck off, Derrick.

20:06.747 --> 20:09.581
Each time, the killer forces entry
via the back door

20:09.625 --> 20:13.414
before making his way through the kitchen
into the rest of the house.

20:14.755 --> 20:17.042
He enters the victim's bedroom
while they sleep,

20:17.091 --> 20:18.457
injects them with a sedative

20:18.509 --> 20:22.719
before butchering them methodically
with some sort of large knife.

20:22.763 --> 20:24.470
Victims are always alone,

20:24.515 --> 20:29.431
implying highly selective identification
of the victims and surveillance.

20:30.479 --> 20:31.936
Oh shit!

20:45.786 --> 20:48.403
Listen, do you think we should
get the press involved now?

20:48.456 --> 20:50.823
Like I don't have enough fucking problems.

20:50.875 --> 20:53.242
DS Binon, a word?

20:53.294 --> 20:55.536
Yeah, you can have two - fuck off!

20:55.588 --> 20:57.671
I just need to talk
to Officer Jackson.

20:57.715 --> 20:59.206
Elliott?

20:59.258 --> 21:01.215
It's all right, this is my nephew.

21:01.260 --> 21:02.671
You okay?

21:02.720 --> 21:05.133
Yeah, there's a man in our village.

21:05.181 --> 21:06.922
I think he's the serial killer.

21:06.974 --> 21:08.090
Right.

21:09.810 --> 21:12.223
He's the local gardener.
I think he killed that woman.

21:13.481 --> 21:15.313
I don't have time for this
right now, okay?

21:15.357 --> 21:16.393
But he's really scary.

21:16.442 --> 21:18.775
Yeah, so's my boss,
but I can't arrest her, can I?

21:18.819 --> 21:20.060
Now, bugger off.

21:30.039 --> 21:31.450
Fuck Derrick!

21:37.797 --> 21:39.413
Yeah fuckin' right. Yeah.

21:48.057 --> 21:50.049
Perfect, of course.

21:53.062 --> 21:54.223
Thanks for stoppin', man.

21:54.271 --> 21:57.184
Been there, right, for ever.
Thought no one was gonna stop.

21:58.317 --> 21:59.524
Right.

21:59.568 --> 22:01.104
Sorry, where is it you're going?

22:01.153 --> 22:02.394
Insane, mate.

22:02.446 --> 22:04.529
- Where?
- Any place but here, yeah?

22:06.700 --> 22:07.941
My name's Lewis, yeah.

22:07.993 --> 22:09.529
Sorry... Tim.

22:11.664 --> 22:13.656
Oh, er, Lewis...

22:13.707 --> 22:16.415
It's just because it's a...

22:16.460 --> 22:19.203
- Uh, it's a company car.
- Company car, thank you.

22:19.255 --> 22:20.541
Sorry.

22:20.589 --> 22:21.921
Thank you.

22:24.927 --> 22:26.509
Fuck it.

22:27.596 --> 22:31.215
So Tim, what do you do,
for a livin', I mean?

22:31.267 --> 22:33.475
I'm a rep for a beer company.

22:33.519 --> 22:34.680
Really?

22:34.728 --> 22:36.094
Yeah, why?

22:36.146 --> 22:37.762
Don't look like the salesman type to me.

22:37.815 --> 22:39.977
I'll take that as a compliment.

22:40.025 --> 22:43.689
Still, it must be great,
all that free booze, eh?

22:43.737 --> 22:45.399
No, I don't drink, so...

22:45.447 --> 22:47.939
You're fucking joking me.

22:47.992 --> 22:49.028
Why?

22:49.076 --> 22:51.113
What's the point havin' a job
selling booze, right,

22:51.161 --> 22:53.995
if you can't take advantage
of the perks, hm?

22:54.039 --> 22:55.746
Yeah, I suppose.

22:55.791 --> 22:58.204
- You hungry?
- Um, but I don't know anywhere

22:58.252 --> 22:59.493
around here that we could, er...

22:59.545 --> 23:02.162
Sure ya do, Timmy.

24:08.739 --> 24:10.071
Hello.

24:11.700 --> 24:13.236
Hi.

24:17.081 --> 24:18.868
Oh no, please don't hurt me!

24:18.916 --> 24:20.748
I've got a wife and kids.

24:20.793 --> 24:22.250
Yeah, of course you do.

24:22.294 --> 24:23.580
Give me your wallet.

24:26.966 --> 24:28.207
PIN number.

24:30.636 --> 24:32.423
And your fucking car keys.

24:32.471 --> 24:34.929
Here, here, here.

24:37.810 --> 24:41.429
Now then, Mr Michael Simpson...

24:41.480 --> 24:43.813
if you breathe a word of this
to the police,

24:43.857 --> 24:47.100
I'm gonna tell your wife and kids
your dirty little secret.

24:48.737 --> 24:50.729
All right, Mickey?

25:44.877 --> 25:46.709
So, let me get this straight.

25:46.754 --> 25:52.500
This Derrick here, this bloodsucking
wanker of a boss, right,

25:52.551 --> 25:54.338
who doesn't give a shit about his staff,

25:54.386 --> 25:56.343
undermines you, right,

25:56.388 --> 26:00.473
makes your work like a twat
night and day, yeah,

26:00.517 --> 26:04.602
and then, right, threatens you with
the sack because he's fucked up?

26:09.860 --> 26:11.442
That's about it.

26:13.363 --> 26:15.275
Pathetic, isn't it?

26:15.324 --> 26:17.190
That's one word for it.

26:17.242 --> 26:20.235
You need to stand up
for yourself, mate, yeah?

