33:48.610 --> 33:50.317
How you doing, kiddo?

33:50.362 --> 33:53.105
Musta been one hell of a party, eh?

33:57.661 --> 33:58.651
So what do you want?

34:02.999 --> 34:04.740
What's your name?

34:04.793 --> 34:08.081
Martine. He's my brother Thomas.

34:10.130 --> 34:11.996
Martine...

34:13.217 --> 34:16.177
We've had... bit of an accident.

34:16.221 --> 34:20.340
We just need somewhere to lay low for
the night and get him stitched up.

34:20.391 --> 34:22.257
Why didn't you go to a hospital?

34:22.310 --> 34:24.677
Well, you see, Thomas,
it's a gunshot wound,

34:24.728 --> 34:26.311
and hospitals have got a funny habit

34:26.356 --> 34:29.268
of calling the police when a patient
rocks up with a gunshot wound.

34:32.404 --> 34:35.021
- Where are your parents?
- Dead.

34:35.072 --> 34:36.655
Anybody else here?

34:38.076 --> 34:40.318
- No one.
- Girlfriend?

34:40.370 --> 34:42.407
Aunts, uncles?

34:42.455 --> 34:44.447
Boyfriend?

34:44.498 --> 34:46.239
No, we live alone.

34:46.293 --> 34:48.409
As I say, we're in a bit of a pickle.

34:48.460 --> 34:49.952
We're not here to hurt you.

34:50.005 --> 34:52.088
I just wanna get him
patched up and lay low.

34:52.132 --> 34:54.715
You help us out, we'll be gone
first thing in the morning,

34:54.759 --> 34:55.795
no harm done, I promise.

34:55.844 --> 34:57.460
No harm done?

34:58.930 --> 35:01.513
You just showed up at our door
wavin' your gun around.

35:01.558 --> 35:04.847
We've got a half dead man
on our dining room table.

35:06.313 --> 35:07.770
You could be anyone.

35:09.357 --> 35:10.814
What's your point?

35:10.859 --> 35:13.397
I don't want you in our house,

35:13.445 --> 35:16.358
I don't want you near my brother,
and I certainly don't want you near me.

35:16.406 --> 35:18.068
Point taken.

35:18.116 --> 35:20.574
We'll be gone in the mornin'.

35:20.619 --> 35:22.030
What do you want us to do?

35:23.913 --> 35:25.279
Can you drive?

35:25.332 --> 35:28.040
- Well, I don't have my licence.
- You're not driving anywhere.

35:28.084 --> 35:29.746
Don't worry about what she's saying.

35:29.794 --> 35:32.286
Are you capable of driving my car
from where it is

35:32.339 --> 35:33.921
to out of sight round the back?

35:35.342 --> 35:36.503
Yeah.

35:36.551 --> 35:38.759
Will you do that for me, please?

35:41.640 --> 35:43.051
Okay.

35:44.517 --> 35:48.557
Martine, I'm gonna need you to get me
some needle, thread, tweezers,

35:48.605 --> 35:51.689
and the sharpest knife
you can find, and...

35:51.733 --> 35:54.817
some of your finest
sanitary towels, please.

35:54.861 --> 35:56.397
Now.

36:50.750 --> 36:52.332
You are joking.

36:52.377 --> 36:53.618
No.

36:53.670 --> 36:57.334
You really gonna take a bullet out of his
shoulder with a craft knife and tweezers?

36:57.382 --> 36:58.714
Yeah.

36:58.758 --> 37:02.672
And you're gonna stitch him up
with fishing wire and a tampon?

37:02.721 --> 37:04.087
Tampon?

37:04.139 --> 37:05.721
- Yeah.
- Cool.

37:05.765 --> 37:08.007
Agh, fuckin' hell!

37:08.059 --> 37:10.597
I'm just cleanin' it, mate,
I'm just cleanin' it.

37:13.773 --> 37:16.311
- Drink some of this.
- You sure about this?

37:19.988 --> 37:22.526
Not really mate, but what the fuck else
we gonna do?

37:29.289 --> 37:32.782
- Woo, you ready?
- Yeah.

37:32.834 --> 37:34.826
- Let's fuckin' do it.
- Wait.

37:34.878 --> 37:37.291
Wait, have you done this before?

37:37.338 --> 37:38.874
No.

37:38.923 --> 37:42.257
Well, then, give it to me.
I've got training.

37:42.302 --> 37:43.463
- Really?
- Yes.

37:43.511 --> 37:45.503
Well, what sort of training you got?

37:45.555 --> 37:47.512
You like a doctor, a nurse or something,
what?

37:47.557 --> 37:48.673
Vet.

37:48.725 --> 37:50.307
Sorry, did you say vet?

37:50.351 --> 37:52.092
- Yes.
- Right.

37:53.521 --> 37:55.513
You did something like this before?

37:57.358 --> 37:58.474
Similar.

38:00.361 --> 38:02.353
On horses.

38:02.405 --> 38:04.146
Horses?

38:28.723 --> 38:30.259
Got it.

38:40.652 --> 38:42.359
Thanks for that.

38:42.403 --> 38:43.769
Thanks a lot.

38:45.406 --> 38:48.149
I, er, I need a phone.

38:48.201 --> 38:50.989
But I can't find one.
I've been lookin' everywhere.

38:51.037 --> 38:53.370
We don't have a phone, it got cut off.

38:53.414 --> 38:55.030
Right.

38:55.083 --> 38:57.450
Where's the nearest phone box then?

38:59.587 --> 39:01.795
About a mile and a half down the road.

39:03.716 --> 39:05.252
You got a car?

39:10.431 --> 39:13.299
My mum's old Jeep is
parked around the back.

39:14.435 --> 39:16.392
Good, okay, good.

39:17.438 --> 39:19.020
We leave in five minutes.

39:19.065 --> 39:20.977
Do I have a choice?

39:21.025 --> 39:22.687
No, no you don't.

39:26.197 --> 39:27.904
Farmhouse?

39:27.949 --> 39:30.111
- Anybody hurt?
- Yeah he's hurt pretty bad.

39:31.202 --> 39:33.194
<i>Will he make it?</i>

39:33.246 --> 39:36.785
Yeah, he's tough as old boots.
He's gonna make it, but...

39:36.833 --> 39:38.825
We can't hang around here.
We need an out.

39:41.296 --> 39:44.460
Turn your phone on at 7.00am
for 10 minutes.

39:44.507 --> 39:45.873
I'll text you details.

39:45.925 --> 39:48.133
Oh, and Dexter, don't trust anyone.

39:49.304 --> 39:52.047
Yeah, I hear you.
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

40:09.657 --> 40:12.240
So word from the boss.

40:12.285 --> 40:15.744
You find Dex and his bum boy Al...

40:15.788 --> 40:17.871
you keep his share of the money.

40:19.042 --> 40:20.874
How much?

40:20.919 --> 40:24.879
Don't know, the bastards bumped us
before we got a chance to count it.

40:24.923 --> 40:28.382
But about six million
supposedly in the van.

40:30.970 --> 40:32.177
Al was injured.

40:32.221 --> 40:35.931
Now, if I was injured, I'd hole up
somewhere unexpected for the night,

40:35.975 --> 40:39.184
get myself sorted then I'd push on
in the morning.

40:40.313 --> 40:44.478
Got a couple of shots in the fuel tank,
so they wouldn't have got far.

40:46.319 --> 40:48.185
It's a pretty isolated area.

40:49.364 --> 40:51.401
Just do the rounds.

41:01.918 --> 41:03.784
So what's your story?

41:07.006 --> 41:08.417
Why do you wanna know?

41:11.094 --> 41:14.713
Well, you've taken my brother and I
hostage in our own home.

41:14.764 --> 41:17.427
I think we deserve some kind
of explanation.

41:18.893 --> 41:20.805
Yeah, fair enough.

41:22.730 --> 41:27.270
Um, I guess what you really need to know
is that Al and I pulled a job today.

41:28.611 --> 41:32.150
Our associates were greedy
and they tried to kill us.

41:33.825 --> 41:36.238
Didn't work, but Al did get shot

41:36.285 --> 41:39.619
and that is how we came to be
at your house tonight.

41:40.665 --> 41:42.372
And I'm truly sorry about that.

42:07.400 --> 42:08.982
Nice watch.

42:09.027 --> 42:11.269
Thanks, my girlfriend...

42:11.320 --> 42:14.688
Sorry, my ex-girlfriend gave it to me.

42:14.741 --> 42:16.448
That was nice of her.

42:16.492 --> 42:17.778
Shame though.

42:17.827 --> 42:19.443
What is?

42:19.495 --> 42:21.452
Girl like that bought me a watch,

42:21.497 --> 42:24.285
I'd be pretty pissed off
if she then dumped me.

42:24.333 --> 42:25.790
As it happens, I dumped her.

42:25.835 --> 42:27.451
Why?

42:27.503 --> 42:29.290
I don't wanna talk about it.

42:29.338 --> 42:31.421
She, er, stole money off ya?

42:32.717 --> 42:33.707
No.

42:33.760 --> 42:36.468
She fucked your best friend?

42:38.389 --> 42:40.130
- Did you fuck her best friend?
- No!

42:40.183 --> 42:41.390
Well, what then?

42:42.560 --> 42:45.473
If you must know, she wasn't a virgin.

42:46.981 --> 42:49.564
And that makes a difference to you?

42:49.609 --> 42:51.896
Yes, it does.

42:51.944 --> 42:56.689
Let me, er... explain a little theory
of mine to ya.

42:59.410 --> 43:02.448
Suppose all you'd ever eaten
was McDonald's,

43:02.497 --> 43:04.955
you were very happy with your McDonald's,

43:04.999 --> 43:08.413
until one day you walk past a Burger King.

43:08.461 --> 43:10.578
Now these Burger Kings look great,

43:10.630 --> 43:12.872
but you stay loyal to your McDonald's,

43:12.924 --> 43:17.339
so you walk away and try to forget
these other burgers.

43:17.386 --> 43:21.551
But sooner or later curiosity
gets the better of ya.

43:21.599 --> 43:23.591
Curiosity killed the cat.

43:23.643 --> 43:25.600
But you see what I'm getting at.

43:25.645 --> 43:28.308
Burgers are a metaphor for dicks, right?

43:28.356 --> 43:30.393
Something like that, yeah.

43:31.901 --> 43:35.520
- Adele's a vegetarian.
- Then you're screwed.

43:35.571 --> 43:37.733
Your friend Al, is he dangerous?

43:38.908 --> 43:41.116
I mean, is Thomas gonna be okay there?

43:41.160 --> 43:42.822
Al wouldn't hurt a fly.

43:44.288 --> 43:46.280
A gangster that wouldn't hurt a fly?

43:46.332 --> 43:49.700
Seriously, Al never really hurt anybody.

43:49.752 --> 43:51.744
Except for his stepdad that time.

43:51.796 --> 43:54.709
Don't move a fucking muscle.

43:55.883 --> 43:59.217
Oz, long time no see.

43:59.262 --> 44:00.969
Just come out the Scrubs.

44:01.013 --> 44:02.470
Workin' for Fordy, eh?

44:02.515 --> 44:04.051
Time bein'.

44:04.100 --> 44:05.762
Where's the fuckin' money?

44:05.810 --> 44:06.971
Beats me.

44:07.019 --> 44:11.138
Dex left me with the kid and his sister,
took the money and ran.

44:11.190 --> 44:13.056
Don't talk shit.

44:13.109 --> 44:14.850
You two is tight as a duck's ass.

44:14.902 --> 44:17.565
And if I didn't know you better,
I coulda swear you two were queer.

44:17.613 --> 44:19.730
Now, where is he?

44:19.782 --> 44:21.819
What happened to his stepdad?

44:21.868 --> 44:25.452
This guy had been beating and bullying Al
and his mum for years.

44:25.496 --> 44:27.954
One time, Al comes home...

44:27.999 --> 44:31.083
Now, Al loves his mum, loves his mum,

44:31.127 --> 44:33.414
so he decides to try and intervene.

44:33.462 --> 44:36.045
But he can't handle this guy,
he's just a kid right?

44:36.090 --> 44:37.831
So...

44:37.884 --> 44:39.796
